I use the bookmarklet here:

https://news.ycombinator.com/bookmarklet.html

But when I submit, the page only has the URL of the page I'm submitting and NOT THE TITLE.

Anyone else experiencing this?
stories.title: Ask HN: Is the Hacker News bookmarklet broken?

stories.text:
Hello,

I would like to ask for your feedback on a website I've been working on. I recently developed a Spotify playlist sharing forum ( https://sharelist.org).

The site functions as a social board where users can share and review playlists. The long-term goal is to create an active community for individuals to find new music they enjoy. The website is currently in beta, and I hope to launch soon. Please let me know your honest opinion and any thoughts on room for improvement!

Site to test: https://sharelist.org

(Note: So sorry for the repost! This was my first time using Hacker News and I meant for the post to go in the Ask HN section, I didn't realize adding a URL would put the post in another section. My apologies!)

Thank you so much.
stories.title: Feedback on Playlist Sharing Website
